Zenbu

Zenbu is a devtools plugin and runtime layer for building model-generated tools inside your app. You use your project as normal. Zenbu adds the ability to create tools on the fly — without leaving your codebase.

You can spawn a devtool to inspect a specific component, log a network interaction, or patch a broken state. Tools run inside your app, using your context. You don’t need to open another tab.

The UI below shows a workspace of devtools running inside a single site:

Tools can read DOM, patch functions, track performance, or talk to the server. They are just apps — you can generate them, edit them, and reuse them across workspaces.

Install

Add Zenbu to any Next.js project:

npm install zenbu
npx zenbu setup

The system runs locally. No login. No dashboard. Everything is editable.
